The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                                 
	 Aptos (US): Somdev Dev Varman scored a facile win over wildcard Alex Kuznetsov to move to the singles quarter finals of the $75,000 ATP Challenger tournament here. The sixth seed Indian hardly broke a sweat in beating the American 6-1, 6-3 in the second round. Somdev next faces South African Izak Van Der Merwe in the last-eight stage.         
	 New Delhi: Four Indians cruised to the singles pre-quarter finals of the Asian Junior Badminton Championship in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia. Advancing in the mens singles event were H.S. Prannoy and Sumeeth Reddy while among women Sikki Reddy and Saili Rane made the next stage.        
	 New Delhi: Promising paddler Soumyajit Ghosh and G. Sathiyan have been included in the 16-member Indian squad for the 15th Asian Junior Table Tennis Championship to be held in Jaipur from July 22.        
	 Taipei: The 100-strong Chinese delegation boycotted the opening ceremony of the World Games in Taiwan on Thursday, underscoring the limits of the historic breakthrough in relations between Taipei and Beijing.  
	While the Chinese delegation did not say immediately why it boycotted the ceremony the act is almost certainly related to President Ma Ying-jeou rsquo;s role in declaring the games open.      
	 Faenza (Italy): Formula One team Toro Rosso fired French driver Sebastien Bourdais on Thursday, ending a disappointing brief stint in the sport for the former four-time Champ Car series winner.        
	 New Delhi: Two members of the Indian football team lost their valuables in a burglary at their hotel in Barcelona on Wednesday. The team is currently preparing in the Spanish city for the forthcoming Nehru Cup in Delhi. While striker Abhishek Yadav found his laptop missing, defender Deepak Mondal lost his mobile phone.        
	 New Delhi: Ian Stillie, who served as the CEO of Scottish first division side Motherwell FC for 14 months till October last year, is among the candidates for the general secretarys post of the All India Football Federation.        
	 Rio de Janeiro: Brazil great Romario was released from jail on Wednesday, a day after being arrested in a child support case involving his first wife.        
	London: Aston Villa have completed the pound;12 million ($19.69 million) signing of England midfielder Stewart Downing from Middlesbrough, the clubs announced on Thursday                                                                                                                                                                   
